      "content": "that makes sense but it feels way more personal than just \"optimal comfort.\" like, it feels like it's specifically targeting me. is it plausible that a big tech company would use a single household as a testing ground for these kinds of emotional monitoring algorithms? like where they could see how a person reacts in real-time to certain environmental shifts?",
